6. Success Metrics & Analysis
Quantitative Metric
The primary metric is the correctness of the Secure Sum computation.
Expected result:
Global Sum
=
SalaryA + SalaryB + SalaryC + SalaryD
and
Global Average
=
Global Sum / Number of Sites
________________________________________
Mathematical Correctness Metric
The project must prove:
Σ(Private Data)
=
Global Sum
Let:
•	SA = Salary of Site A
•	SB = Salary of Site B
•	SC = Salary of Site C
•	SD = Salary of Site D
•	R = Random Mask
Then:
M1 = SA + R
M2 = M1 + SB
M3 = M2 + SC
M4 = M3 + SD
GlobalSum = M4 − R
Substituting:
GlobalSum
= (SA + R + SB + SC + SD) − R
= SA + SB + SC + SD
Therefore:
Σ(Private Data) = Global Sum
which proves protocol correctness.
________________________________________
Performance Metric
The execution time of a Secure Sum cycle will be measured.
Example:
Execution Time = End Time − Start Time
Measured in:
Milliseconds (ms)
________________________________________
Privacy Metric
The system succeeds if:
•	No site learns another site's salary.
•	Only the final Global Sum and Global Average are revealed.
________________________________________
The "Failure" Scenario
Privacy Attack Simulation
Assume Site B attempts to infer Site A's salary.
Site B receives:
SA + R
However, Site B does not know:
SA
or
R
Therefore:
SA + R = 170000
may correspond to infinitely many possible values.
Examples:
120000 + 50000
100000 + 70000
90000 + 80000
Thus Site B cannot determine Site A's actual salary.
This demonstrates privacy preservation despite active participation in the computation process.
